{{Infobox bus accident |title = 2015 Tanzania road accident |image = Tanzania Iringa location map.svg |caption = Location of Iringa Region in Tanzania |date = 11 March 2015 |location = [[Iringa Region]] |country = Tanzania |line = |operator = |owner = |type = |cause = |buses = 1 |other = |pax = |peds = |deaths = 41 |injuries = 23 |damage = |property = }}
[[File:Location Tanzania AU Africa.svg|250px|thumbnail|right|Location of Tanzania in Africa]]
The '''2015 Tanzania road accident''' occurred on 11 March 2015 when a bus and two lorries collided in [[Tanzania]]. At least 41 people died and another 23 were wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-31837200|title=Tanzania bus crash leaves dozens dead in Iringa|work=BBC News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/africa/2015/03/dozens-dead-tanzania-road-collision-150311131127979.html|title=Dozens dead in Tanzania road collision|work=aljazeera.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/03/11/us-tanzania-crash-idUSKBN0M71EE20150311|title=Tanzania bus collision kills at least 41, toll could rise|work=Reuters}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2015/03/11/world/africa/11reuters-tanzania-crash.html|title=Tanzania Bus Collision Kills at Least 41, Toll Could Rise|date=11 March 2015|work=Reuters|accessdate=16 July 2016|via=The New York Times}}</ref> The accident took place in [[Iringa Region]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2015/03/11/world/africa/ap-af-tanzania-accident.html|title=Police: 41 People Dead in Tanzania Road Accident|date=11 March 2015|work=AP|accessdate=16 July 2016|via=The New York Times}}</ref>
