'''Freedom and Constitution Day''' ({{lang-tr|27 Mayıs Hürriyet ve Anayasa Bayramı}}) was a former [[public holidays in Turkey|public holiday in Turkey]] celebrated on 27 May between 1963 and 1981 in commemoration of the 27 May 1960 military coup and the new constitution.
By the [[1960 Turkish coup d'état|1960 military coup]] on 27 May, the [[11th Parliament of Turkey|11th Parliament]] was abolished. On 9 July 1961, a [[Turkish constitutional referendum, 1961|referandum]] was held for a new [[Turkish Constitution of 1961| constitution]], and on 15 October 1961 Turkey returned to democratic political system.<ref>[http://ahmetsaltik.net/tag/hurriyet-ve-anayasa-bayrami/ Ahmet Saltık’s essay in Aydınlık newspaper {{tr icon}}]</ref> On 4 April 1963, a public holiday was enacted to commemorate the new constitution. <ref>[http://haber.sol.org.tr/devlet-ve-siyaset/27-mayis-ta-neler-oldu-haberi-28835 Solhaber news {{tr icon}}]</ref> The holyday was on the 27 May. The public holiday was abolished on 17 March 1981 following the [[1980 Turkish coup d'état|12 September 1980 military coup]].
