{{short description|2017 wildfire in San Luis Obispo County, California.}} {{Infobox wildfire | title = Hill Fire | image = | caption = | cost = | injuries = | fatalities = | reference = <ref name=CalFire>{{cite web|title=Hill Fire|url=http://www.fire.ca.gov/current_incidents/incidentdetails/Index/1588|website=[[CalFire]]|accessdate=June 26, 2017}}</ref> <!-- ONLY FOR INDIVIDUAL FIRES --> | date = {{Start date|2017|06|26}} – {{End date|2017|6|30}} | location = [[San Luis Obispo County, California|San Luis Obispo County]], [[California]] | coordinates = {{coord|35.40|-120.4992|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = USA California Southern | pushpin_map_caption = Location in Southern California | area = {{Convert|1,598|acre|km2|0}} | buildings = 4 | cause = | landuse = | perps = | motive = }}
The '''Hill Fire''' was a [[wildfire]] in 2017, east of [[Santa Margarita, California|Santa Margarita]] near [[California State Route 58|Highway 58]] in [[San Luis Obispo County]], [[California]]. The fire burned an estimated 1,598 acres and destroyed four homes.
==The fire== The fire started near Park Hill Road and La Entrada about 3:30 p.m. Monday, June 26, and expanded to 1,200 acres throughout the course of the day.<ref name="LA Times-Mandatory evacuations">{{cite web|last1=Serna|first1=Joseph|title=Mandatory evacuations ordered as wildfire in San Luis Obispo County destroys one building|url=http://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-ln-hill-fire-slo-county-20170627-story.html |work=[[The Los Angeles Times]]|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref> Evacuations were ordered for over 100 residents in the area of Huer Huero Road to Highway 58, including Black Mountain Resort, Blue and Blue Ridge roads.<ref name="LA Times-Mandatory evacuations"/> The fire destroyed three structures also reportedly destroying actor [[Johnny Galecki]]’s ranch home.<ref name="Tribune Hill Fire">{{cite web|last1=Ferreira|first1=Gabby|title=Hill Fire destroys 3 structures but won’t grow any larger, Cal Fire says|url=http://www.sanluisobispo.com/news/local/article158610479.html |work=[[The_Tribune_(San_Luis_Obispo)|The Tribune]]|access-date=27 June 2017}}</ref> The fire was contained on June 30.<ref name=CalFire/>
