The '''Mobile Motion Film Festival''' is a new [[film festival]] in [[Switzerland]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p02s7kp9 |title=BBC Travel Show ||accessdate=2 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.blick.ch/sonntagsblick/guenstiger-naeher-besser-handyfilme-erobern-die-kinos-id8365262.html |title=Blick ||accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref> The festival was founded in 2014 by [[Andrea Holle]] and [[Simon Horrocks]], with money raised via [[kickstarter.com]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/thirdcontact/bring-mobile-motion-film-festival-to-life|title=Bring Mobile Motion Film Festival to life!|accessdate=2 February 2017}}</ref> To be selected for the festival films must have been shot using smartphones or other mobile devices and must be no longer than 10 minutes.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://t.cineman.ch/news/die-sieger-des-1-momo-film-festival/12058/ |title=Die Sieger des 1. MoMo Film Festival |publisher=Cineman |accessdate=28 November 2015}}</ref>
